Embodiments of the present invention facilitate parallel
distributed computing. During operation, embodiments of
the present invention receive from a requesting node an
operator o₁
and unevaluated expressions representing argu-
ments for that operator. Next, embodiments of the invention
evaluate the arguments and then determine another unevalu-
ated expression based on that operator and the evaluated
arguments. Subsequently, embodiments of the invention
send the another evaluated expression to other nodes for
evaluation and receive the resulting evaluated expression,
which is then returned to the requesting node.
